From this first linear regression, it seems that â(Intercept)â, Trafficâ, âTypeâ, âUrbanâ, âLengthâ, âLimitâ, âSlopeâ and âWidthâ are significant. However, the Adjusted R-squared is very small, which may indicate that this model is not appropriate.
Let us now look what problems we might have :

Here, it seems that there is a pattern appearing when few accidents occurs, thus independence of the residuals \(r\) and the fitted values \(\hat{y}\) might fail.

Here, the pattern suggest that \(var(r)\) might increase with the mean increasing. Not good eitherâ¦
